30/12/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Turkish police detained 19 people Saturday (December 29th) believed to be linked to al-Qaeda. A large amount of weapons, ammunitions, false documents and organisational documents were confiscated during the arrests, which were carried in four cities -- Aksaray, Istanbul, Ankara, and Adana. The police have monitored the group for over three months and received information the suspects were training for possible terror attacks. (AFP, Reuters, Press TV, Focus - 30/12/07) 
